cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.LG 

This paper analyzes gendered communities on social platforms, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as sentiment analysis and text similarity measures. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses user demographics and social values, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The focus on community identity and attitudes suggests cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques for sentiment analysis could also relate to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
